Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for Next.js
================================================

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the BremBot crypto signal dashboard.

Changes Made:
-------------

1. Installed Dependencies:
   - Added @vercel/speed-insights package (v1.3.1) via npm
   - Updated package.json with the new dependency
   - Updated package-lock.json with resolved dependencies

2. Modified Files:
   - app/layout.tsx
     * Imported SpeedInsights component from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'
     * Added <SpeedInsights /> component inside the <body> tag, after {children}

Implementation Details:
----------------------

Since this project uses Next.js 15.5.10 (which is newer than 13.5) with the App Router:
- Used the import from '@vercel/speed-insights/next' (optimized for App Router)
- Added the component directly to the root layout without needing 'use client' directive
- Placed the component inside the body tag, after the children, following best practices

The SpeedInsights component will now automatically collect and report Web Vitals metrics 
(Core Web Vitals like LCP, FID, CLS, etc.) when the application is deployed on Vercel.

Verification:
-------------

✅ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
✅ Linter passed with no errors (npm run lint)
✅ All dependencies properly installed and lock file updated
✅ Existing code structure preserved - only added necessary changes

The implementation is production-ready and will start collecting performance metrics 
once deployed to Vercel.
